title: Rooney, Bulldogs Pick Up First WCHA Win
text:
Rooney, Bulldogs Pick Up First WCHA Win 
By Zach Schneider October 16, 2015 Updated Oct 16, 2015 at 9:55 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Maddie Rooney made 10 saves to earn her first career collegiate victory on Friday night as the University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) women's hockey team beat MSU-Mankato 4-2 at AMSOIL Arena. 
Katherine McGovern scored the only goal in the first two periods, with that coming on the power play early in the first period. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
From there, the two teams exploded for five combined goals in the third period --- UMD's came from Lara Stalder, Morgan Morse, and Catherine Daoust. 
Rooney was pretty solid throughout in her third collegiate start, with those 10 saves including one on a penalty shot midway through the second period. 
UMD is now (3-4-0) overall this season, with game two of the series coming Saturday at 3:07 p.m. at AMSOIL Arena.
